abstract.1: andalucia (album)<Andalucia_(album)> is the fourth studio album<Studio_album> by los angeles tito & tarantula<Tito_&_Tarantula>3 band tito & tarantula<Tito_&_Tarantula>, released in tito & tarantula<Tito_&_Tarantula>1
abstract.2: the album<Studio_album> marked several line-up changes in the band, which had previously consisted of lead singer/rhythm guitarist tito larriva, lead guitarist peter atanasoff, and drummer johnny "vatos" hernandez
abstract.3: andalucia (album)<Andalucia_(album)> album<Studio_album> featured the debut of lead guitarist steven hufsteter – who had previously played with larriva in the cruzados, bassist io perry, and keyboardist marcus praed
abstract.4: the band toured promoting the album<Studio_album> for several years
abstract.5: they also filmed a music video for the song "california girl"
abstract.6: however, upon seeing how bad the footage of the video was, perry threw up, larriva threatened to quit, and atanasoff was not seen around for days
abstract.7: so, to compensate, larriva made his own video for the song using the eight dollars he had in his pocket
abstract.8: in the last 40 seconds of the song "effortless", larriva, atanasoff, and perry can be heard laughing while they watch the "california girl" music video
abstract.9: the song "la flor de mal" is a cover of a cruzados song that larriva and hufsteter wrote when they were in the cruzados

abstract.1: available in all colours<Available_In_All_Colours> is the debut album<Album> of one minute silence<One_Minute_Silence>, released in 1998
abstract.2: available in all colors<Available_in_All_Colors> was released on big cat records<Big_Cat_Records>, and distributed by 3mv/pinnacle in the uk, sony music<Album> in france, rough trade in germany and austria, m
abstract.5: in scandinavia, record<Album> services in ireland, p
abstract.8: s in benelux and universal in italy
abstract.9: available in all colors<Available_in_All_Colors> was produced by machine, and so, although one minute silence<One_Minute_Silence> are a rap metal<Rap_metal> band, it has a hip hop quality to it
abstract.10: the album<Album> features cover artwork by anne stokes (the copyright is owned by big cat records<Big_Cat_Records>, however) which portrays fetuses in orange and green tubes with the labels "racist", "prophet", "anarchist", "humanitarian", "psychopath", "dictator", etc
abstract.11: available in all colors<Available_in_All_Colors> is intended as a comment on the isolation of capitalist society and the categorization of individuals
abstract.12: three songs of available in all colors<Available_in_All_Colors> are featured in the 1999 video game twisted metal 4; "south central" is played in the opening cinematic, "a more violent approach" serves as the menu music<Album>, and "and some ya lose" is used as the sixth level theme (the oil rig)
abstract.13: all of them are instrumental versions

abstract.1: atrocities (album)<Atrocities_(album)> was christian death's fourth album and the first with valor kand taking over main duties after rozz williams' departure
abstract.2: the album's subject matter deals almost exclusively with the holocaust including songs about auschwitz and josef mengele
abstract.3: recorded at rockfield studios<Studio> in monmouth, wales it also featured the songwriting and arrangement skills of barry galvin, who, along with johann schumann, would leave the group upon the completion of atrocities (album)<Atrocities_(album)> - both went on to form mephisto walz
